HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 561
By Reneau
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Carl Elzia Levi of
Chattanooga.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly were greatly saddened to learn of
the passing of Carl Elzia Levi; and
WHEREAS, Carl Levi was an exemplary public servant and consummate professional
who worked assiduously to improve the quality of life for his fellow citizens in numerous
capacities; and
WHEREAS, Carl Levi served with acumen and alacrity with the City of Chattanooga and
Hamilton County for more than fifty years, having been originally hired by then-Chattanooga
Mayor Rudy Olgiati for what was supposed to be a six-week tenure; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Levi served as deputy city clerk from 1957 to 1961 before becoming
assistant city treasurer; he was named city treasurer in 1978 and won the respect and
admiration of his colleagues and the citizens of Chattanooga during his tenure in that office,
from which he took his much-deserved retirement on December 31, 2001; and
WHEREAS, seeking to continue his public service, Carl Levi was elected to the post of
Hamilton County trustee in August 2002, and he served two terms in that esteemed position
before ending his service in 2010, having introduced a number of cost-saving measures and
other operational innovation to benefit local taxpayers; and
WHEREAS, known by many for his distinguished military career, Carl Levi joined the
U.S. Army as a private in 1952 during the Korean War and was commissioned as a second
lieutenant in artillery in 1958; and
WHEREAS, transferring from active duty, Mr. Levi served in various positions in the
National Guard and retired at the rank of brigadier general in the Tennessee National Guard in
1987; and
